tonnage of all Malaysian airports]] after [[Kuala Lumpur International Airport]].<ref name=\"Penang International Airport\" /> {{As of|2017}}, the airport posted a record 7.23 million tourist arrivals.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite journal|title=Penang International Airport factsheet|url=http://www.malaysiaairports.com.my/factsheet/pdf_pdf_pdf_penangairport2015_1429833711_1234570707_457272701.pdf|journal=[[Malaysia Airports]]}}</ref>\n[[File:9M-FYC Penang.jpg|alt=|thumb|ATR 72-500 of Firefly air company standing at Penang international airport]]\nNotably, [[Malaysia Airlines]] subsidiary, [[Firefly (airline)|Firefly]], has made Penang International Airport one of its main hubs. [[AirAsia]], another domestic [[Low-cost carrier|budget airliner]], also operates out of Penang International Airport as one of its secondary hubs.<ref name=\"btimes\" />\n{|class=\"toccolours sortable\" style=\"padding:0.5em;\"\n|+ '''Annual passenger numbers and aircraft statistics\n! | <center>Year</center>\n! | <center>Passengers<br />handled\n! | <center>Passenger<br />% change</center>\n! | <center>Cargo<br />(tonnes)</center>\n! | <center>Cargo<br />% change</center>\n! | <center>Aircraft<br /> movements</center>\n! | <center>Aircraft<br />% change</center>\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n|2003||2,334,669||{{nochange}}||197,567||{{nochange}}||30,558||{{nochange}}\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n|2004||2,987,993||{{increase}} 28.0||212,369||{{increase}} 7.5||33,069||{{increase}} 8.2\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n|2005||2,834,545||{{decrease}} 5.1||221,971||{{increase}} 4.5||34,616||{{increase}} 4.7\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n|2006||3,103,772||{{increase}} 9.5||225,952||{{increase}} 1.8||36,259||{{increase}} 4.7\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n|2007||3,173,117||{{increase}} 2.2||208,582||{{decrease}} 7.7||39,265||{{increase}} 8.3\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n|2008||3,405,762||{{increase}} 7.3||192,936||{{decrease}} 7.5||43,796||{{increase}} 11.5\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n|2009||